{
  "doc_id": "49327",
  "text": "ZnO is a wide-band-gap semiconductor with an energy gap of 3.37 eV at room temperature. Many different ZnO structures have been investigated for solar cell applications [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Since ZnO shows different chemical and physical properties depending on the size and shape of NCs, it might easily form a penetration network between particles; this is greatly beneficial for charge carrier transportation.",
